{"meta": {"centerNodeId": "taxonomy-species-eubucco-bourcierii", "centerNodeType": "taxonomy", "generatedAt": "2026-05-28T16:28:22", "includedNodeCount": 3, "includedLinkCount": 2, "layoutMode": "precomputed-static"}, "center": {"id": "taxonomy-species-eubucco-bourcierii", "name": "Red-headed barbet", "type": "taxonomy"}, "nodes": [{"id": "taxonomy-genus-eubucco", "name": "Eubucco", "latinName": "Eubucco", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "Eubucco（Eubucco）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联4种鸟类，如Lemon-throated barbet、Scarlet-hooded barbet、Red-headed barbet等4种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 4, "x": 488.02, "y": 191.3, "z": 59.9}, {"id": "taxonomy-species-eubucco-bourcierii", "name": "Red-headed barbet", "latinName": "Eubucco bourcierii", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "Red-headed barbet（Eubucco bourcierii）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如Red-headed barbet。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": -158.79, "y": -167.46, "z": 364.57}, {"id": "bird-red-headed-barbet-886e63f3", "name": "Red-headed barbet", "englishName": "Red-headed barbet", "latinName": "Eubucco bourcierii", "type": "bird", "status": "LC", "summary": "The red-headed barbet (Eubucco bourcierii) is a species of bird in the family Capitonidae, the New World barbets. It is found in Costa Rica, Guyana, Panama, Venezuela, Colombia, Ecuador and Peru. Taxonomy and systematics The red-headed barbet has six subspecies: E. b. salvini Shelley (1891) E. b. anomalus Griscom (1929) E. b. occidentalis Chapman (1914) E. b. bourcierii Lafresnaye (1845) E. b. aequatorialis Salvadori & Festa (1900) E. b. orientalis Chapman (1914) Description Male red-headed barbet subspecies except E. b. occidentalis range in weight from 30 to 41 g (1.1 to 1.4 oz). Females except occidentalis weigh 31 to 38 g (1.1 to 1.3 oz). Male occidentalis weigh 37.8 to 45.1 g (1.33 to 1.59 oz) and females 37.8 to 43.7 g (1.33 to 1.54 oz). Males have a red head, an orange to yellow breast, and a white belly. A white collar separates the head from the olive green back. The amount of red on the throat and chest and the width of the orange-yellow breast band vary among the subspecies. The female's crown and nape vary from dull orange to shades of green among the subspecies. Several have a black forehead. Its back is green, the throat grayish yellow with a yellow to orange band below it. Its lower breast is olive-yellow and the belly white. As in the male, there is some variation among subspecies. Distribution and habitat The subspecies of the red-headed barbet are found thus: E. b. salvini, Costa Rica and western Panama E. b. anomalus, eastern Panama and probably adjacent northwestern Colombia E. b. occidentalis, both slopes of Colombia's Western Andes E. b. bourcierii, Andes of western Venezuela, the east slope of Colombia's Central Andes, and both slopes of Colombia's Eastern Andes E. b. aequatorialis, coastal mountains and the western slope of the Andes in Ecuador E. b. orientalis, eastern slope of the Andes in Ecuador and northern Peru The red-headed barbet inhabits the interior and borders of evergreen mountain primary forest and also adjacent secondary forest. The species' overall elevational range is 400 to 2,400 m (1,300 to 7,900 ft) but there are large geographic variations. Behavior Feeding The red-headed barbet's diet has not been studied in detail, but it is known to include arthropods such as caterpillars and adult insects and fruit such as berries and (at feeders) bananas. Breeding Little has been published about the red-headed barbet's breeding phenology. Like other New World barbets, they excavate cavities in trees and sometimes in fence posts. The clutch size is two to five; the female incubates at night and both sexes do so during the day. Vocalization The red-headed barbet's song has been described as \"a resonant, ventriloquial, somewhat toad-like trill krrrrrrrrrrr\" [1]. Some calls have been described as \"grunts and snarls\" [2]. Status The IUCN has assessed the red-headed barbet as being of Least Concern. \"Although the overall population trend is believed to be one of decline, the rate of decline is not thought to be a cause for concern.\" References", "shortSummary": "The red-headed barbet (Eubucco bourcierii) is a species of bird in the family Capitonidae, the New World barbets. It is found in Costa Rica…", "locations": ["哥斯达黎加", "圭亚那", "巴拿马", "委內瑞拉", "哥伦比亚", "厄瓜多尔", "原始森林", "次生林"], "lat": 10.0, "lng": -84.0, "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b7/Red-headed_barbet_%28Eubucco_bourcierii_aequatorialis%29_male_Paz_de_las_Aves.jpg/960px-Red-headed_barbet_%28Eubucco_bourcierii_aequatorialis%29_male_Paz_de_las_Aves.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-eubucco", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-eubucco-bourcierii", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-eubucco", "species": "taxonomy-species-eubucco-bourcierii"}, "expandable": true, "x": -158.79, "y": -167.46, "z": 367.54}], "links": [{"key": "bird-red-headed-barbet-886e63f3__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-eubucco-bourcierii", "source": "bird-red-headed-barbet-886e63f3", "target": "taxonomy-species-eubucco-bourcierii", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-eubucco-bourcierii__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-eubucco", "source": "taxonomy-species-eubucco-bourcierii", "target": "taxonomy-genus-eubucco", "relation": "belongs_to_genus", "label": "属于属", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 分类字段补充：Red-headed barbet 属于属 Eubucco。"}]}
